Chukwudi Akasike, Port Harcourt Fire has gutted an oil facility belonging to the Nigerian Agip Company in Ubeta community, Ahoada East Local Government Area of Rivers State. It was gathered that the fire outbreak at the oil installation was said to have started on Thursday, even as the cause of the inferno remained unknown as of Friday. It was learnt that the inferno had caused panic among indigenes of the community. READ ALSO: No going back on cashless policy — CBN Our correspondent gathered that Joint Investigating Visit (team) is trying to ensure that the fire is put out. When contacted, the Port Harcourt Zonal Director of National Oil Spill Detection Response Agency, Cyrus Nkangwung, said he was informed about the incident at 3:00 a.m. on Friday. “There was a fire outbreak. It happened on Thursday night. I got the information around 3:00 a.m (on Friday). Efforts are ongoing to put out the fire; even the JIV team is on the ground,” he said. 